 Three friends ended up in hospital after ordering a ‘fish bowl’, spiked with Flakka, at a Pinetown bar. Rising Sun Chatsworth reports that the men started behaving bizarrely with friends and family saying that they were frothing at the mouth, climbing trees and walls and hallucinating. They quoted one of the victims saying “when his wife arrived at the hospital, he could not control his actions and bit her hand so hard that a chunk of her flesh fell off.” Read the full story here by Rising Sun Chatsworth.   